      <para id="id3531021">When I say this is a “matrix” I’m referring to the numbers in boxes. The labels (such as “Granger, H” or “Poison”) are labels that help you understand the numbers in the matrix, but they are not the matrix itself.</para>
      <para id="id3523637">Each student is designated by a <emphasis>row</emphasis>. A row is a horizontal list of numbers.</para>
      


<exercise id="id90909898098"><problem id="idp1280352">
